[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pedestrian seriously hurt after being struck by bus

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A pedestrian has been seriously injured after she was struck by a bus in north London in the early hours.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Officers were called just before 01:00 GMT on Saturday to Rosebery Avenue in Islington.
Metropolitan Police said the driver of the bus did not stop at the scene after the collision, but he has been traced. No arrests have been made as yet.
The 47-year-old injured woman was taken to hospital where she is in a serious but stable condition.
